OVEMENTSince launch, we‚Äôve continuously improved our mattress based on research, data, and feedback from our community of more than 400,000 customers. These updates include adding a fourth layer to increase pressure relief, developing proprietary foams for added durability and breathability, and creating a removable cover that‚Äôs easier to clean.8,109+25,000+700+Average star ratings based on listed sources. Updated 04/24/17See how we evaluate our productsOur R&D team uses three main methods to inform product improvements:USER TESTINGIn the beginning, we created beta models and invited friends and seasoned snoozers to A/B test them. We continue to enlist Casper customers to test improvements.DURABILITY TESTINGWe do feel testing, force profile testing, airflow testing, rebound testing, compression testing... well, you get the idea. Finally, we simulate 10 years of sleep to make sure it will last and last.RESEARCHOur dedicated research team conducts interviews and runs studies to understand sleep habits. These learnings help us make products that reflect real people‚Äôs needs.‚ÄúSupremely comfortable‚ÄùCOOL BY DESIGNUnlike traditional memory foam mattresses, the Casper is designed to help you sleep cool. The open-cell top layer uses convection and conduction to flow heat away from your body. Similarly, the memory foam layer leverages airflow to pull heat out of the top layer, leaving you cool and comfortable.Why does heat flow matter?While you‚Äôre asleep, your body acts like a little thermal engine, putting out the equivalent heat of a 100W light bulb. By using foams that leverage convection (heat transfer through air) and conduction (heat transfer through solids), we‚Äôre able to pull heat away from your body, and disperse it back into the atmosphere.LESS STORES, MORE SNORESWe flipped the mattress industry on its head by eliminating showrooms, employing smart logistics, and using compression technology to ship the Casper mattress in a compact box. This allows us to offer a premium mattress for a fraction of the price.Red door with Casper Mattress boxRed door with Casper Mattress box‚ÄúChanging the way people shop for mattresses‚Äù100 NIGHT TRIAL, FREE RETURN PICKUPSleep on it, lounge on it, dream on it ‚Äî if you don't love it, we'll give you a full refund. No springs attached.Order OnlineFree Shipping100 Nights, Free Return PickupEXPLORE THE TRIALBUILD YOUR BEDTHE WATERPROOF MATTRESS PROTECTORGuards against dirt, spills, and normal wear and tearShopTHE FOUNDATIONProvides excellent support and can be assembled in minutesShopTHE METAL BED FRAMEWorks with our foundation to create a complete sleep setupShopFREQUENTLY ASKED QUESTIONSWhat setup do you recommend for the Casper mattress?We designed the Casper mattress to be versatile, so it can work with all standard foundations. As with all foam beds, you want as much direct support under the mattress as possible. A wooden slatted or platform bed offers the most support. For optimal support under all size sizes ( twin, twin XL, full, queen, king, Cal king ) , we suggest using the Casper foundation.Why is the Casper mattress better than its lookalikes?The engineering behind the Casper mattress goes far beyond aesthetics. Our mattress is the result of intensive research and continuous development by our 30-person San Francisco R&D team, who collectively hold more than 50 patents. Unlike putting a cover over an off-the-shelf construction, our approach allows us to quickly respond to customer feedback and continually enhance our mattress. As a result, the Casper mattress has received high praise from Consumer Reports, was named one of Time magazine‚Äôs best inventions, and holds multiple industrial design awards.Does the Casper mattress have any safety or environmental certifications?All the foams in the Casper mattress are CertiPUR-US¬Æ  certified. These foams are made without ozone depleters, PBDE flame retardants, mercury, lead and other heavy metals, formaldehyde, phthalates regulated by the Consumer Product Safety Commission. They are Low VOC (Volatile Organic Compound) emissions for indoor air quality (less than 0.5 parts per million).SEE ALL MATTRESS FAQSTalk to a human, not a botChat with UsCall or text us+1 888-498-0003YOUR CARTYour Cart Is EmptySHOP NOWGot questions? Our snooze specialists are ready to chat.






















